@pchalasani I added a simple example. It's a chatbot about langroid dependencies. The user needs to specify package name, then relevant packages and their versions will be identified from the graph DB and forwarded to LLM to get some description about them.
Docker isn't required, but Neo4j cloud access is needed instead. Though it should work with both.
The example can be greatly improved, this is just a simple version to chat about dependency in one round.

Just tried it with package chainlit, then it waited a long time, and then I get several repeated errors like this --
openai.BadRequestError: Error code: 400 - {'error': {'message': "Invalid parameter: only messages with role 'assistant' can have a function call.", 'type': 'invalid_request_error', 'param': 'messages.[1].function_call', 'code': None}}

not sure if this is related to the neo4j agent or something within langroid ChatAgent
